      <item>
        <title>Implementation of Retention time Aware Intelligent DRAM Refresh in DDR4</title>
        <description>&lt;ul&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;
    &lt;h4 id=&quot;problem--refresh-operations-interfere-memory-accesses-and-waste-energy&quot;&gt;Problem : Refresh operations interfere memory accesses and waste energy&lt;/h4&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;
    &lt;h4 id=&quot;observation--energy-and-performance-overhead-caused-by-refresh-operations-rised-when-the-device-integrity-increased&quot;&gt;Observation : Energy and performance overhead caused by refresh operations rised when the device integrity increased&lt;/h4&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;
    &lt;h4 id=&quot;idea-applied-different-refresh-rate-for-strong-dram-cells-idea-from-raidrisca2012&quot;&gt;Idea: Applied different refresh rate for strong DRAM cells (idea from &lt;a href=&quot;http://localhost:4000/img/RAIDR.pdf&quot;&gt;RAIDR(ISCA’2012)&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/h4&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;
    &lt;h4 id=&quot;implementation--bloomfilter-to-store-the-information-of-weak-rows-in-memory-controller-ddr4-2133-configuration-file&quot;&gt;Implementation : Bloomfilter to store the information of weak rows in memory controller, DDR4-2133 configuration file&lt;/h4&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;
    &lt;h4 id=&quot;evaluation--used-dramsim2-and-gem5-as-simulators-memory-intensive-benchmarks-from-spec-cpu2006&quot;&gt;Evaluation : Used DRAMSim2 and gem5 as simulators, memory intensive benchmarks from SPEC CPU2006&lt;/h4&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;
    &lt;h4 id=&quot;contribution--came-up-with-the-result-that-raidr-averaged-12-performance-improvement-over-auto-refresh-scheme-in-ddr4&quot;&gt;Contribution : Came up with the result that RAIDR averaged 12% performance improvement over auto-refresh scheme in DDR4&lt;/h4&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;
    &lt;h4&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://localhost:4000/img/RAIDR_CONFIG.PNG&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;
    &lt;h4 id=&quot;-1&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://localhost:4000/img/RAIDR_RESULT.PNG&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

</description>
